Class AbstractResultSetConverter

java.lang.Object
  org.openadaptor.auxil.connector.jdbc.reader.AbstractResultSetConverter
All Implemented Interfaces:

Direct Known Subclasses:
ResultSetToOrderedMapConverter, ResultSetToXMLConverter
public abstract class AbstractResultSetConverter
extends java.lang.Object
implements IResultSetConverter

Abstract base class which converts a SQL ResultSet into a format for use within an adaptor. Subclasses defined the output type.

Author:
higginse, browe (updated based on Brian's patch suggestions)

setUseColumnLabels

public void setUseColumnLabels(boolean useColumnLabels)
If true, use column labels if available in returned ResultSets.
The default is false for backwards compatibility with openadaptor 3.3

Parameters:
useColumnLabels - boolean to indicate labels may be used.

getUseColumnLabels

public boolean getUseColumnLabels()
Flag to indicate if column aliases may be used in returned ResultSets.

convert

public java.lang.Object[] convert(java.sql.ResultSet rs,
                                  int maxBatchSize)
                           throws java.sql.SQLException
If maxBatchSize is a positive number convert not more than the maxBatchSize of rows in the result set. If maxBatchSize equal to zero or less - convert all rows in the result set.

Specified by:
convert in interface IResultSetConverter
Parameters:
rs - Contains the current ResultSet
maxBatchSize - sets upper limit on number of records which may be converted from the ResultSet.
Returns:
Object[] array with entries for each row returned
